{"ID":270018, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"18\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs17.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs19.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 18<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">glory to Him, for the hour of His judgment is come.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> Repent ye, repent ye, and embrace the\n  everlasting covenant,<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> and flee to Zion,<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> before the overflowing scourge<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> overtake you, for there are\n  those now living upon the earth whose eyes shall not be closed in death until they see all these\n  things, which I have spoken, fulfilled. Remember these things; call upon the Lord while He is near,\n  and seek Him while He may be found,<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> is the exhortation of your unworthy servant.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"right\">(Signed) JOSEPH SMITH, JUN.&mdash;DHC 1:312-316.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Important Correspondence With the Brethren in Zion<\/div>\n  <p class=\"summary\">The &ldquo;Olive Leaf&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> is the name given by the Prophet to the wonderful revelation known as Sec. 88, in the <i>Doctrine<\/i>\n  <i>and Covenants<\/i>. There are few, if any, revelations given to the Church&mdash;and to the world if the world will receive\n  them&mdash;greater than this &ldquo;Olive Leaf, plucked from the Tree of Paradise.&rdquo;  In this letter to W. W. Phelps, one of the\n  presiding brethren in Missouri, the Prophet raises a warning voice based upon the word of the Lord as revealed in the\n  revelation and correspondence from Missouri.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"salutation\"><div class=\"salutation\">Brother William W. Phelps:<\/div><div class=\"placeDate\">Kirtland, January 14, 1833.<\/div><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">I send you the &ldquo;olive leaf&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> which we have plucked from the Tree of Paradise,<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> the Lord&rsquo;s\n  message of peace to us; for though our brethren in Zion indulge in feelings towards us, which are\n  not according to the requirements of the new covenant,<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> yet, we have the satisfaction of knowing that\n  the Lord approves of us,<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> and has accepted us, and established His name in Kirtland<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> for the\n  salvation of the nations;<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> for the Lord will have a place whence His word will go forth,<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> in these\n  last days, in purity; for if Zion will not purify herself,<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> so as to be approved of in all things,<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> in His\n  sight, He will seek another people;<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> for His work will go on until Israel is gathered,<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> and they who\n  will not hear His voice,<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> must expect to feel His wrath.<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> Let me say unto you, seek to purify\n  yourselves,<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> and also the inhabitants of Zion,<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> lest the Lord&rsquo;s anger be kindled to fierceness.<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">A Warning to Zion<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Repent, repent, is the voice of God to Zion;<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span> and strange as it may appear, yet it is true,\n  mankind will persist in self-justification until all their iniquity is exposed, and their char-<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110812\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110812)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110812)\">Rev. 14:7<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114259\"><a href=\"javascript:v